    "body": "I'm still confused why this is needed. I've been running a node on a FreeBSD machine for years, and never had to redefine `MAKE`.\r\n\r\nA clean checkout of master on FreeBSD 12.0-RELEASE-p10:\r\n```\r\nuser@medea:~/src/bitcoin % echo $MAKE\r\nMAKE: Undefined variable.\r\nuser@medea:~/src/bitcoin % ./autogen.sh\r\n\u2026\r\nuser@medea:~/src/bitcoin % ./configure --disable-wallet --disable-dependency-tracking\r\nchecking build system type... amd64-unknown-freebsd12.0  \r\nchecking host system type... amd64-unknown-freebsd12.0\r\n\u2026\r\nuser@medea:~/src/bitcoin % gmake -j4\r\n\u2026\r\nuser@medea:~/src/bitcoin % size src/bitcoind\r\n     text    data     bss       dec        hex   filename\r\n  5594825   59184   19896   5673905   0x5693b1   src/bitcoind\r\n```\r\n\r\nDo you need this when building other autoconf projects as well? If not, I wonder what is different in our build system.",
